    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Modest Beginning</h2>  
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Treehotel's mission has always been to provide guests with a hotel experience beyond the ordinary. The founders, Kent Lindvall and Britta Jonsson-Lindvall, were two seemingly ordinary locals from Swedish Lapland, deeply rooted in their home village of Harads. <strong>So when they set out to create something newer, they naturally wanted it to be in Harads</strong>, a place they loved.
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/britta-jonsson-kent-lindvall-treehotel-sweden-founders.png" alt="Britta Jonsson (left) and Kent Lindvall (right) are founders of Treehotel, Sweden" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>Britta Jonsson (left) and Kent Lindvall (right) are founders of Treehotel, Sweden. Credits: hospitalitydesign.com</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Oddly enough, neither had any initial plans to enter the hotel business. <strong>Britta was a nurse, Kent a counselor, and both had full schedules</strong>. Yet, they were endlessly resourceful, always looking for ways to do more with what they had. Kent ran a company that organized international fishing trips, while Britta worked on various development projects. They shared a passion for their village and a desire to create a livelihood there.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Britta's entrepreneurial instincts led her to an old 1920s retirement home that had been abandoned for years. In 2004, <strong>the couple purchased and renovated it, transforming it into a charming bed and breakfast place, <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-05-04-2025-1-brittas-pensionat" target="_blank">Britta‚Äôs Pensionat</a></strong>. The guesthouse had a nostalgic 1930s-1950s ambiance, with a bar, restaurant, sauna, and modern conveniences like TV and internet. While it was a labor of love, it wasn‚Äôt exactly a goldmine. Something had to change.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column> 
    </mj-section>


